name: docker-map
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "docker-map" %}
{% set version = "1.0.0" %}

package:
  name: "{{ name }}"
  version: "{{ version }}"

source:
  url: "https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz"
  sha256: "200aa8231ed06ccf35145f148c6e816463bd4492481908cf513a3b3016485933"

build:
  number: 0
  noarch: python
  script: "{{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv"

requirements:
  host:
    - pip
    - python
    - six
  run:
    - python
    - six
    - docker-py

test:
  imports:
    - dockermap
    - dockermap.build
    - dockermap.client
    - dockermap.map
    - dockermap.map.action
    - dockermap.map.config
    - dockermap.map.policy
    - dockermap.map.runner
    - dockermap.map.state
    - dockermap.map.state.update
    - tests

about:
  home: "https://github.com/merll/docker-map"
  license: "MIT"
  license_family: "MIT"
  license_file: "LICENSE"
  summary: "Managing Docker images, containers, and their dependencies in Python."

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - kszucs
smithy_version:
No azure token. Create a token and
put it in ~/.conda-smithy/azure.token
